<TITLE> 2 killed as train slams truck in Shampur </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)At least two people were killed and another four seriously injured as a train slammed into a truck at Baraitala 'rail crossing' in Shampur, southwest Dhaka. "The crossing is not an authorised level crossing and has no guard stationed there," Railway Police sub-inspector Mizanur Rahman told bdnews24.com. The SI said the Dhaka-bound train, leaving Narayanganj at 9.05pm, ploughed into the truck at around 9.30pm. One of the dead was identified as 'Moksedul' (25); the other, also a young man in his twenties, remained unidentified up to Sunday midnight, said the police officer. The injured were admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, he said. bdn
